column1: "plt.title('Physical Health Days vs Mental Health Days')\n"
"#Question 1:Physical Health Days vs Metal Health Days"

"In the scatter plot PhysicalHealthDays vs MentalHealthDays the relationship between the two variables seems to show a positive moderate relationship. Meaning that those who report increased number of days experiencing poor physical health also report a higher number of days with poor mental health. Nevertheless
column2: even if the association is far from perfect (and supported by the presence of some cases with dozens of mental health days but relatively few physical health days)
column3: overall data are more consistent. The dataset contains outliers meaning there are few points which do not follow the general trend. So all this shows is that there is a general association
column4: and not even a tight one
column5: which means that these pineapple eating men may also simply be on the luckier end of the health days spectrum for other reasons."

column1: " #Question2: Does alcohol consumption significantly impact the likelihood of developing heart disease?"
"The plot shows that relationship between heart disease and alcohol consumption. So unless the bar for consumers is a whole lot higher in the \"Yes\" category
column2: we can conclude that drinking alcohol increases the probability of heart disease. So
column3: if non-drinkers have a taller bar in the Yes category
column4: then it means non-drinkers are more likely to get heart disease. If the relationship between drinking status and heart disease prevalence is not significant
column5: we would instead expect very little difference in the height of the bars. All in all the plot gives a visual indication of this and further statistical testing can be used to give more concrete answers."
